This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommender systems and collaborative filtering algorithms. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it discusses the credibility of voting users and their similarity to the target user. Additionally, it could be classified under the Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC) sub-category as it relates to trust and reputation in online commerce. The Database (cs.DB) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper deals with sparse matrices and prediction algorithms. Finally, the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category may be relevant as the paper discusses trust inference and the potential for misleading recommendations.
